data.title: Church of Ireland - Succession List Tuam, Limerick and Killaloe Diocese
data.meta_description: Wiki page on Church of Ireland Tuam Limerick and Killaloe Succession in Ireland.
data.text: 1839The Metropolitan rank and rights of the see of Tuam were extinguished, and it became the Bishopric of Tuam, Killala and Achonry 2022.Tuam, Killala and Achonry merged with Limerick and Killaloe to form bishopric of Tuam, Limerick and Killaloe 1839.Killala and Achonry merged to become Tuam, Killala and Achonry 2022.Limerick and Killaloe merged with Tuam, Killala and Achonry to form bishopric of Tuam, Limerick and Killaloe 1976.Killaloe and Clonfert merged with Limerick, Adfert & Aghadoe to form bishopric of Limerick and Killaloe 1834.Clonfert and Kilmacduagh was merged to become Killaloe, Kilfenora, Clonfert and Kilmacduagh 1834Killeloe and Kilfenora merged to become Killaloe, Kilfenora, Clonfert and Kilmacduagh. 1663.Ardfert and Aghadoe merged to become Limerick, Ardfert and Aghdoe 1987.Ardfert merged with Limerick to become Dean of Limerick and Ardfert 1987.Limerick merged with Ardfert to beome Dean of Limerick and Ardfert 17551757About 1755-7, some dispute arose about the presentation, and the dignity remained vacant for some years.
